          },
          "answerKey": {
            "modelAnswer": "Red blood cells carry oxygen because they contain the pigment haemoglobin, which binds oxygen and transports it around the body.",
            "keyPoints": ["contains haemoglobin", "binds oxygen", "transports oxygen"]
          }
        },
        {
          "marks": 2,
          "displayOrder": 2,
          "mandatory": true,
          "maxWordLimit": 120,
          "question": {
            "question_text": "Name the four chambers of the human heart and identify where oxygenated blood is received and pumped out.",
            "question_type": "short_answer",
            "difficulty_level": "Easy",
            "exam_type": "EXAM_PREP",
            "exam_year": 2026,
            "exam_paper": "ICSE Grade 5 Science Chapter Review",
            "is_pyq": false,
            "tierLevel": "BEGINNER",
            "tierOrder": 2,
            "max_marks": 2,
            "points": 2
          },
          "answerKey": {
            "modelAnswer": "The four chambers are the right atrium, right ventricle, left atrium, and left ventricle. The left atrium receives oxygenated blood from the lungs and the left ventricle pumps it out to the body.",
            "keyPoints": ["right atrium/ventricle", "left atrium/ventricle", "oxygenated blood enters left atrium", "left ventricle pumps to body"]
          }
        },
        {
          "marks": 2,
          "displayOrder": 3,
          "mandatory": true,
          "maxWordLimit": 130,
          "question": {
            "question_text": "Describe the pathway of oxygenated blood starting from the lungs until it reaches the body cells.",
            "question_type": "short_answer",
            "difficulty_level": "Easy",
            "exam_type": "EXAM_PREP",
            "exam_year": 2026,
            "exam_paper": "ICSE Grade 5 Science Chapter Review",
            "is_pyq": false,
            "tierLevel": "BEGINNER",
            "tierOrder": 3,
            "max_marks": 2,
            "points": 2
          },
          "answerKey": {
            "modelAnswer": "Oxygenated blood travels from the lungs to the left atrium via the pulmonary veins, moves into the left ventricle, and is pumped through the aorta into arteries that carry it to body cells.",
            "keyPoints": ["pulmonary veins", "left atrium", "left ventricle", "aorta to body cells"]
          }
        },
        {
          "marks": 5,
          "displayOrder": 4,
          "mandatory": true,
          "maxWordLimit": 300,
          "question": {
            "question_text": "Explain double circulation and why it is important for humans.",
            "question_type": "long_answer",
            "difficulty_level": "Medium",
            "exam_type": "EXAM_PREP",
            "exam_year": 2026,
            "exam_paper": "ICSE Grade 5 Science Chapter Review",
            "is_pyq": false,
            "tierLevel": "INTERMEDIATE",
            "tierOrder": 4,
            "max_marks": 5,
            "points": 5
          },
          "answerKey": {
            "modelAnswer": "Double circulation means blood flows through the heart twice in each circuit: once through the pulmonary circulation (heart to lungs and back) and once through systemic circulation (heart to body). It keeps oxygen-rich and oxygen-poor blood separate, allowing efficient oxygen delivery to all tissues.",
            "keyPoints": ["two loops", "pulmonary loop", "systemic loop", "keeps blood separate", "efficient oxygen delivery"]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
